### English Title:
Concerns Raised by President Trump in Financial Markets

### English Text Summary:
The article discusses the significant concerns raised in financial markets by President Donald Trump, particularly after he announced tariffs on various countries. It explains key financial terms such as stock market crash, bear market, recession, and tariffs. A stock market crash occurs when stock values drop suddenly, often due to panic selling. A bear market is characterized by a prolonged decline in stock prices. Recession is defined as a period of economic decline, while depression occurs when GDP falls significantly over an extended period. The article also elaborates on tariffs, which are taxes imposed on imported goods, and the concept of reciprocal tariffs promoted by Trump, where countries imposing tariffs on U.S. goods can expect similar measures in return.

